		<td><b>Re: How well can Metal Slug backgrounds be recreated with ti</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That game is supposedly 708 Mbit; I'm guessing this means 8 MB was dedicated to code.<br /><br />I wonder what sort of compression ratio you'd get on that data with an S-DD1?  Not that I seriously expect Metal Slug 3 to fit in an S-DD1 cart without altering the pinout of the chip or adding a helper chip.  Theoretically I think it can address 256 MB, and I know for a fact that at least one 64 MB homebrew ROM exists, but physically it seems to be limited to 16 MB...<br /><br />I was referring to the original Metal Slug, which is 193 Mbit.  Metal Slug 2 (362 Mbit) might fit as well, but it looks much tighter...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


